fession|journal=Law & Social Order|year=1969|volume=161|url=http://heinonline.org/HOL/LandingPage?collection=journals&handle=hein.journals/arzjl1969&div=19&id=&page=}} {{Subscription}} * {{cite book|last=Przeklasa Jr|first=Terence Robert|title=The band, the bureau, and the business interests: the Mission Indian Federation and the fight for the Agua Caliente Indian Reservation|year=2011|publisher= [[California State University, Fullerton|California State University]] (Masters thesis)|location=Fullerton, CA|pages=141 |oclc=767861063}} * {{cite book|last=Schlesinger|first=Robert A.|title=The California Indian Lease (California Continuing Education of the Bar: Practice Book No. 35)|year=1967|publisher=Regents of the University of California|location=Berkeley, CA|pages=152|oclc=885954|lccn=67064477}} * {{cite book|title=Land allotments on Agua Caliente Reservation, CA: hearing before a special subcommittee of the Committee on Interior and Insular Affairs, House of Representatives, 85th Congress, 1st session, on equalization of land allotments|year=1958|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|location=Washington, DC|pages=116|author=U.S. Congress. House. Committee on Interior and Insular Affairs|format=book and microfilm|date=October 2, 1957|oclc=31124883}} * {{cite book|last=Wiefels|first=Howard H.|title=The Indian Land Zoning Controversy in Palm Springs|date=June 3, 1976|pages=99}} (Wiefels was [[List of Mayors of Palm Springs, California|Mayor]] of Palm Springs from April 1967 to March 1974.)
