{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}} <!-- [[Image:ICon 2005 Sign.jpg|thumb|200px|right|The sign at the entrance to the Israeli ICon 2005 Convention]] -->
'''ICON''' is the name of at least five [[science fiction convention]]s. In order of seniority, these are:
* '''[[ICON (Iowa science fiction convention)]]''' is held in the [[Cedar Rapids, Iowa|Cedar Rapids]]/[[Iowa City, Iowa|Iowa City]] area since 1975, usually in late October or early November, under the auspices of the Mindbridge Foundation, a not-for-profit foundation which also sponsors the [[Gamicon]] and [[AnimeIowa]] conventions. * '''[[I-CON]]''' is held in [[Stony Brook, New York]], every spring, on the campus of the [[State University of New York at Stony Brook]] since 1981. '''I-CON''' (with a hyphen) is short for '''I'''sland '''Con'''vention – a reference to its location on [[Long Island]]. * '''[[ICON festival]]''' is the main [[Israel]]i annual science fiction, [[fantasy]] and [[roleplaying games|role-playing]] convention (now officially a festival) – standing for '''I'''sraeli '''Con'''vention. It has been held in [[Tel Aviv]] annually since 1996 during [[Sukkot]]. * '''Icon''' was the name of the 2005 National Science Fiction Convention in [[New Zealand]]. * '''iCON''' is an annual science fiction, [[fantasy]] and [[roleplaying games|role-playing]] convention in [[Turkey]], [[İstanbul]] held by the Science Fiction and Fantasy Club of [[İstanbul University]] .
==External links== *[http://www.iowa-icon.com/ Iowa Icon home page] *[https://web.archive.org/web/20120302021754/http://iconsf.org/ New York I-CON home page] *[http://www.icon.org.il/ Israeli ICon home page] *[http://icon.sf.org.nz/ New Zealand Icon home page] *[http://www.iubkfk.com/icon/ İstanbul CON- iCON home page]
