|{{sort|1978-05-24|May 24, 1978}}
|[[United States Penitentiary, Marion]]
|{{flag|United States}}
| style="background-color: #F2CECE;"| No
|align=left|[[Garrett Brock Trapnell]]<br />Martin Joseph McNally<br />James Kenneth Johnson
|43-year-old Barbara Ann Oswald hijacked a [[St. Louis, Missouri|Saint Louis]]-based charter helicopter and forced the pilot to land in the yard at USP Marion. While landing the aircraft, the pilot, Allen Barklage, who was a [[Vietnam War]] veteran, struggled with Oswald and managed to wrestle the gun away from her. Barklage then shot and killed Oswald, thwarting the escape.<ref name="St. Joseph News-Press">{{cite news |ref=harv|title= Plane Hijacked|first= |last=St. Joseph News-Press|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=nadeAAAAIBAJ&sjid=YFMNAAAAIBAJ&pg=1758,5387939&dq=barbara+ann+oswald+helicopter&hl=en|newspaper=[[St. Joseph News-Press]] |publisher=[[News-Press & Gazette Company]] |location= |isbn= |issn= |oclc= |bibcode= |doi= |id= |date=December 21, 1978 |at=Front Page  |accessdate= January 10, 2011 |language= |quote= }}</ref>  A few months later Oswald's daughter [[TWA Flight 541|hijacked TWA Flight 541]] in an effort to free Trapnell.
