|{{sort|1987-12-10|December 10, 1987}}
|[[Gartree (HM Prison)]]
|{{flag|United Kingdom}}
| style="background-color: #CEF2CE;"| Yes
|{{sortname|Sydney|Draper|nolink=1}}<br />John Kendall
|At 3:16&nbsp;p.m. on December 10, 1987, John Kendall and Sydney Draper were sprung from [[Gartree (HM Prison)|Gartree's]] exercise yard with the aid of a hijacked [[Bell 206|Bell 206L helicopter]]. Kendall was a gangland boss serving eight years while Draper was jailed for murder and serving a life sentence.<ref name="Gartree">{{cite web | date = October 3, 2006 | url = http://www.harboroughmail.co.uk/features/Prison-official-recounts-jailbreak-in.1800769.jp| title =Helicopter escape still remembered 19 years on| publisher =[[Johnston Press|Johnston Press Digital Publishing]] | accessdate = May 14, 2009 }}</ref>  The escape caused great controversy at the time and led to a tightening of security at the jail. Kendall was recaptured 10 days later but Draper remained at large for 13 months.
