| Pilot Charles Bella was hired to fly a real estate agent around the Santa Fe area. As he was flying his Aerospatiale Gazelle helicopter she pulled a gun and forced him to land in the courtyard of the [[New Mexico State Penitentiary riot|Santa Fe prison]]. Three inmates jumped in and he flew the aircraft to another site, pursued by a US Customs Service helicopter that was later joined by a state police helicopter. Pursuing helicopters claimed that Bella tried to force them down through aggressive maneuvers. However, they were able to tail him and police were waiting for the helicopter every time it touched down.<ref name="Blade_1988"/><ref name="LA TIMEs 1988">{{cite web |ref=harv|date= July 12, 1988|url = http://articles.latimes.com/1988-07-12/news/mn-5714_1_helicopter-service|title = Two Inmates Recaptured After Chases in Air, on Ground : Three Escape New Mexico Prison in Helicopter|format = |publisher = Times Staff Writer| accessdate = June 8, 2014 | last=Kennedy| first= J. Michael|quote=}}</ref> Two of the prisoners, Francis Mitchell and Randy Lackey, were captured almost right away while Danny Mahoney was later captured with assistance from a canine unit.<ref name="Blade_1988"/>
