|{{sort|2009-07-23|July 23, 2009}}
|Bruges 
|{{flag|Belgium}}
| style="background-color: #CEF2CE;"| Yes
|{{sortname|Ashraf |Sekkaki|nolink=1}} plus three other criminals
|A man hijacked a helicopter and forced its pilot to land in a prison outside the city of [[Bruges]]. The helicopter picked up four men including Ashraf Sekkaki, a 26-year-old convicted bank robber who has been described as one of the most dangerous criminals in Belgium. Sekkaki escaped from another prison in 2003. The escapees then flew to the town of [[Aalter]], then seized a black Mercedes from its female driver and robbed a service station before heading for the Belgian coast.<ref name="Reuters_2009">{{cite news |date= July 24, 2009|url = http://in.reuters.com/article/entertainmentNews/idINIndia-41276520090723|title = Three escape Belgian jail in hijacked helicopter|publisher = Reuters| accessdate = July 23, 2009 | last= |quote=}}</ref> He was captured in Morocco two weeks later.<ref name="Flandersnews_2009">{{cite web|date = August 9, 2009|url = http://www.deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws.english/news/1.577492|title = Moroccan police capture Ashraf Sekkaki|publisher = [[Flandersnews]]|accessdate = January 21, 2010|last = |quote = |deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100118113106/http://www.deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws.english/news/1.577492|archivedate = January 18, 2010|df = }}</ref> 
