{{Current}} {{Infobox MMA event |name=UFC Fight Night: Blaydes vs. Ngannou 2 |image= [[File:UFCFightNight141poster.jpeg|225px]] |promotion=[[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] |date={{start date|2018|11|24}} |venue=[[Cadillac Arena]] |city=[[Beijing]], China |attendance= |gate= |previousevent=[[UFC Fight Night: Magny vs. Ponzinibbio]] |followingevent=[[The Ultimate Fighter: Heavy Hitters#The Ultimate Fighter 28 Finale|The Ultimate Fighter 28 Finale]] }}
'''''UFC Fight Night: Blaydes vs. Ngannou 2''''' (also known as '''''UFC Fight Night 141''''') is an upcoming [[mixed martial arts]] event produced by the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] that will be held on November 24, 2018 at [[Cadillac Arena]] in [[Beijing]], China.<ref name="FNBeijing">{{Cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2018/8/5/17652994/ufc-to-debut-in-beijing-on-nov-24|title=UFC to debut in Beijing on Nov. 25|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Newswire|date=2018-08-05|access-date=2018-08-05}}</ref>
==Background== The event will mark the promotion's first visit to Beijing. The UFC previously visited [[Mainland China]] for [[UFC Fight Night: Bisping vs. Gastelum]] in November 2017.
A heavyweight rematch between former [[UFC Heavyweight Championship]] challenger [[Francis Ngannou]] and [[Curtis Blaydes]] is expected to serve as the event headliner.<ref name="BeijingME">{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/mma/story/_/id/24393887/beijing|title=UFC heavyweights Francis Ngannou, Curtis Blaydes to meet in Beijing|publisher=espn.com|author=Ariel Helwani|date=2018-08-16|accessdate=2018-08-16}}</ref> The pairing met previously in April 2016 at [[UFC Fight Night: Rothwell vs. dos Santos]], with Ngannou winning the fight via TKO stoppage at the conclusion of the second round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxsports.com/ufc/story/ufc-francis-ngannou-beats-curtis-blaydes-after-nasty-eye-injury-stops-the-fight-041016|title=Francis Ngannou beats Curtis Blaydes after nasty eye injury stops the fight|publisher=foxsports.com|author=Damon Martin|date=2016-04-10|accessdate=2018-08-16}}</ref>
Shana Dobson was scheduled to face Wu Yanan at the event. However, Dobson pulled out of the fight in mid-October citing an injury and was replaced by Lauren Mueller.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2018/10/lauren-mueller-replaces-shana-dobson-vs-wu-yanan-ufc-fight-night-141|title=Lauren Mueller replaces Shana Dobson vs. Wu Yanan at UFC Fight Night 141|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Staff|date=2018-10-18|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref>
[[Elizeu Zaleski dos Santos]] was expected to face [[Li Jingliang]] at the event. However, Santos pulled out from the bout on October 27 due to a knee injury.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/platform/amp/2018/10/27/18031786/knee-injury-forces-elizeu-zaleski-out-ufc-beijing-li-jingliang|title=Knee injury forces Elizeu Zaleski out of UFC Beijing|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Guilherme Cruz|date=2018-10-27|access-date=2018-10-27}}</ref> He was replaced by David Zawada.<ref name="ZawadaIn">{{cite web|url=http://mmadna.nl/david-zawada-pakt-short-notice-partij-tegen-li-jingliang-tijdens-ufc-beijing/|title=David Zawada tackles short notice party against Li Jingliang during UFC Beijing|publisher=mmadna.nl|author=Marcel Dorff|date=2018-11-01|accessdate=2018-11-01}} {{nl icon}}</ref>
[[Frankie Saenz]] was expected to face [[Song Yadong]] at the event. However on November 7, it was reported that he pulled out of the bout due to injury and was replaced by promotional newcomer Vince Morales.<ref name="MMADNA2Chinese">{{cite web|url=http://mmadna.nl/chinese-team-alpha-male-vechters-maken-opwachting-tijdens-ufc-beijing/|title=Chinese Team Alpha Male fighters make an appearance at UFC Beijing|publisher=mmadna.nl|author=Marcel Dorff|date=2018-11-07|accessdate=2018-11-07}} {{nl icon}}</ref>
At the weigh-ins, Rashad Coulter weighed in at 208 pounds, 2 pounds over the light heavyweight non-title fight limit of 206. Coulter was fined 20 percent of his purse, which went to his opponent Hu Yaozong.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bjpenn.com/mma-news/ufc/ufc-beijing-weigh-in-results-rashad-coulter-comes-in-heavy/|title=UFC Beijing weigh in results: Rashad Coulter comes in heavy|date=2018-11-23|publisher=bjpenn.com|author=Drake Riggs|access-date=2018-11-23}}</ref>
